OL,3,CBereaved parents secure political
OL,4,Csupport for their 'duty of care' fight
OL,6,FThe parents of a University of Bristol
OL,7,Fstudent who took her own life say they
OL,8,Fhave won a crucial victory in their
OL,9,Ffight to force all higher education
OL,10,Finstitutions to be legally responsible
OL,11,Ffor the care of their students.
OL,13,FBob and Maggie Abrahart have been
OL,14,Fcampaigning for six years since the
OL,15,Fdeath of their daughter Natasha. The
OL,16,Fcouple are calling for a statutory
OL,17,Fduty of care which would make
OL,18,Funiversities legally responsible for
OL,19,Ftaking steps to avoid students coming
OL,20,Fto harm.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/11
