OL,3,CBereaved parents secure political
OL,4,Csupport for their 'duty of care' fight
OL,6,FNatasha's mother Maggie said, "We will
OL,7,Fkeep fighting until we get that
OL,8,Fstatutory right, students aren't being
OL,9,Flooked after right and things are
OL,10,Fgoing wrong, in so many cases
OL,11,Funiversities haven't done what they
OL,12,Fshould have done.
OL,14,F"Universities haven't done what they
OL,15,Freally ought to do, we need to look at
OL,16,Fthings that are careless (and)
OL,17,Fnegligent, where universities haven't
OL,18,Fbothered to do something that you
OL,19,Fwould reasonably expect them to do.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/11
